\f2\i \cf0 How Do I Have The Server Started At System Start-Up?\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\ql\qnatural

\f0\i0 \cf0 \
Most servers will run Rumpus all day, every day to provide 24/7 FTP access for their users. To have Rumpus automatically started when the server is booted, open the "Install Server" window and check the "Launch Rumpus Service At System Startup" checkbox. Note that this will not start the Rumpus control application, only the Rumpus service, when the computer is turned on. In fact, the Rumpus service will be started even if no user logs in to the computer.\
\
The "Launch Rumpus Service At System Startup" checkbox is more than a simple preference setting. When the box is checked, a startup script (and associated "plist" file) is saved to the folder "/Library/StarupItems/Rumpus/", and when it is unchecked, the script is deleted.\
\
